4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists without any prior knowledge. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills in securing these environments.

Participants will learn cloud security, offensive and defensive penetration testing, and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The program also covers data loss prevention strategies and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST.

The bootcamp is 16 weeks long and includes three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required.

For more information, visit their website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity.

